{"title": "Accomplice by Inaction", "content": "Igraine: I never did anything to hurt you! \n\nMorgan: Indeed, my lady. You did nothing. You did nothing when my father had my mother killed so that you could sit in her place. As you did nothing when my father banished me. \n\nIgraine: No queen questions her king. \n\nMorgan: And I thought my opinion of you couldn't get any lower. second scene together \u2014 Starz's Camelot , during Igraine and Morgan'sscene together I never did anything to hurt you!Indeed, my lady. You did nothing. You did nothing when my father had my mother killed so that you could sit in her place. As you did nothing when my father banished me.No queen questions her king.And I thought my opinion of you couldn't get any lower.\n\nSomebody was around as a crime was being committed, but did nothing. Now the victim wants them brought to account.\n\nAudience and writer sympathy for each party (on one hand, the accusers, be they the victim or not, and on the other, the accused) can vary, depending on a variety of factors. The work can evaluate the so-called accomplice's responsibility for the crime simply by establishing whether it was done with the bystander being oblivious or knowing all along. Sometimes, there will be someone to point out that it also depends on whether that character refused to help, was also another innocent victim, or was simply incapable to offer help. Therefore, the accuser can really go anywhere between the top and the lower-middle part of the Sliding Scale of Antagonist Vileness (understandable if not a real Woobie, Destroyer of Worlds) if they are themselves unjust while addressing injustice.\n\nCompare Failure-to-Save Murder, which has a strong overlap rate. Compare and contrast Cruel Mercy, which the non-intervention may be from the point of view of the inactive party, thus making the accusation justified to the most irrational, death-seeking victims.\n\nSee also a common cause for this trope, Moral Myopia, All-Powerful Bystander (who is likely to be seen as this), Lawful Stupid, While Rome Burns and You Were Trying Too Hard, for the almost-opposite. Contrast Murder by Inaction.\n\nPossible overlap with Hitler Ate Sugar and Villain-by-Proxy Fallacy, could involve Insane Troll Logic in some cases.\n\nCompare and contrast With Us or Against Us.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AccompliceByInaction", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Camelot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MakenKi", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MyHeroAcademia", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/EternalSabbath", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/Persona5TheAnimation", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AttackOnTitan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/WITCH", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Marvel2099", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SpiderMan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheTransformersLastStandOfTheWreckers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Watchmen", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/TheLionKingIISimbasPride", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheDarkKnight", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/NightWatch", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheCelebration", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/NaturalBornKillers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BeautyAndTheBeast2017", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ABrothersPrice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DragonBones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Clarissa", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/CelineRaphael", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/LaDemesure", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JaneAusten", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LoveAndFreindship", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/SenseAndSensibility", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MansfieldPark", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Demons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/FyodorDostoevsky", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheFountainhead", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/TheIrregularAtMagicHighSchool", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/StarTrekIIITheSearchForSpock", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/VitaNuova", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Worm", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LeftBehind", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/